The paper discusses the use of compression algorithms for compressed sensing, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The specific examples of compression algorithms and signals mentioned in the paper are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed compressible signal pursuit (CSP) algorithm involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SP).
